The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Saturday, August 30, 2003  Richie Rich lifts Trial 
 BY STAR RACER				 	 Rutherford on Richie Rich, the winner of the Calcutta Colts Trial Stakes at the RCTC Friday				 										Calcutta: Riding a well-judged race, jockey Rutherford Alford partnered his father Richards trainee Richie Rich to an upset victory in the 1,400m Calcutta Colts Trial Stakes on Firday. Available 5-1 in the betting ring, Rutherford had the Batzushka-Grand Start three-year-old settled in the fourth berth before urging him to come with a fine finishing effort in the stretch-run.				 										In the sporting event, the Orange William Cup, Bharath Singhs favourite Allodium beat his stablemate, Alcalde, narrowly after fighting a grim battle with him in the last furlong of the 1,400m race.				 										RESULTS				 										1. Fire Flash Handicap 1,200m: (1-2-6-3) Bright And Clear (Suresh) 1; Juneau (Shanker) 2; Rohini (Surjeet) 3; Onewonone (R. Marshall) 4. Won by: 3-1/2; 3/4; Nk; (1-19.8). Tote: Win Rs 88; Place: 16; 15; 12; Quinella: 195; Shp: 44; Tanala: 1,694. Fav: Onewonone (3). Winner trained by Daniel D.				 										2. Prince Regent Cup 1,800m: (3-6-5-4) Archery (C. Alford) 1; Midas Touch (Yasin) 2; Raring To Go (Salam) 3; Regal Rocket (Jaiswal) 4. Won by: 8-1/4; 2-3/4; 5-1/2; (2-0.1). Tote: Win Rs 14; Place: 15; 27; Quienlla: 55; Shp: 53; Tanala: 226. Fav: Archery (3). Winner trained by Vijay S.				 										3. Saloon Handicap 1,100m: (1-5-4-8) Flying Dash (Yadav) 1; Rhythm Divine (Surender) 2; Castle Moon (Rutherford) 3; Secret Desire (M. Reuben) 4. Won by: 2-3/4; Nk; 4-3/4; (1-13.3). Tote: Win Rs 40; Place: 17; 41; 18; Quinella: 465; Shp: 125; Tanala: 3,734. Fav: Secret Desire (8). Winner trained by E. Bhungard.				 										4. Orange William Cup 1,400m: (4-2-3-5) Allodium (C. Alford) 1; Alcalde (R. Marshall) 2; Alternator (Shanker) 3; Hello Brother (Harish) 4. Won by: Nk; 4-1/4; SH; (1-30.4). Tote: Win Rs 26; Place: 21; 20; Quinella: 45; Shp: 52; Tanala: 302. Fav: Allodium (4). Winner trained by Bharath S.				 										5. Calcutt